item.title: Red Fox In the Snow
item.media:title: Red Fox In the Snow
item.media:description:
Roeselienraimond.com | Facebook | Instagram | PRINT
This particular day was so cold. The wind was heavy and the only way to walk was backwards, as snow was completely blinding my site. Sneaky little snowflakes crawled into my clothes, my camera and my eyes and slowly but surely literally everything was covered with a thick, white layer of snow. My camera became so cold and wet that it became almost totally uncontrollable and so did my fingers.
And yet—at that moment—I wasn't aware of any cold or discomfort. There I was, lying in the snow, with a gorgeous fox in front of me that was just sitting there as if she didn't care about the snow at all. And how could I complain, witnessing a smiling fox bravely defying in a snow storm...?

item.title: Dr Gregory House
item.media:title: Dr Gregory House
item.media:description:
"Better be careful. I have a full bladder and I'm not afraid to use it." - Dr House

lmao, he's so cool

This portrait was a lot of fun to do and I like the final result! The shirt was a pain in the bum, as well as the background, but House himself was just way fun.

Omg he's touching my arm

Why did I get 78 favourites on my WIP 4? Why?!? It wasn't even finished, crazy people!
Or as House would say:
"That's absurd. I love it."


Stuff I used:
  • 4H, H, HB, 2B, 3B mechanical pencils

  • regular and kneaded erasers

  • tissue and tortillions for blending

  • A4 sized sketchbook paper

    • Time spent: approx 18 hours

    Work in progress can be found here:
    WIP 1
    WIP 2
    WIP 3
    WIP 4

    Coming next:
    - Dr Wilson
    - Riku (KH)

These are actually twenty feet taller than the other waterfall - making them sixty feet tall. I also decided not to include any ground in this one.
